<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 31 at 2:33PM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Periods of moderate snow with poor visibility this afternoon
across Central Montana...
At 220 pm, a strong cold front has moved south of Great Falls, but
it will continue to move south through Central Montana through the
afternoon. Temperatures in the 30s ahead of the front will fall
into the 20s behind it.
Periods of moderate snow with the front are being accompanied by
gusty westerly winds shifting northerly behind the front. Gusts
are mostly in the 35 to 45 mph range, but gusts have been reaching
55 mph in some areas.
Accumulations will mostly be less than one inch at lower
elevations, but up to 3 inches are possible in the mountains.
Blowing snow will also reduce visibility to less than one mile at
times.
Be prepared for rapidly changing visibility and road conditions,
as roads may become icy in spots.</description>
